Persuasive effects (Hypothesis H1b-H4b)

H1a: A message including a static minority DSNA is less persuasive than a message without a minority DSNA.

H2b: A message including a dynamic DSNA is more persuasive than a message including a static minority DSNA.

H3b: A message including a dynamic DSNA is more persuasive than a message without a DSNA.

H4b: A message including a majority ISNA is more persuasive than a message without a majority ISNA.
